******
[1] Hebei, Tianjin
Date: Wed 15 Jun 2016 03:43:34 (GMT+8)
Source: CRI English, Xinhua News Agency report [edited]
http://english.cri.cn/12394/2016/06/15/3746s930882.htm


Local health authorities said Tuesday night [14 Jun 2016] that 2 human H7N9 cases have been confirmed in north China's Tianjin Municipality.

The 2 patients are a native of Langfang City in north China's Hebei Province and a local resident from Tianjin's Binhai New Area, said the Tianjin Municipal Health and Family Planning Commission.

They were hospitalized in Tianjin after developing serious pneumonia. Both of them had contact with diseased poultry. The 2 cases were isolated, according to the commission.

H7N9 is a bird flu strain first reported to have infected humans in March 2013 in China. It is most likely to strike in winter and spring.

[Web editor: Luo Bin]

