******
[2] Hebei, Beijing
Date: Wed 15 Jun 2016 13:50
Source: Xinhua News Agency [in French trans. Corr.SB, edited]
http://french.xinhuanet.com/2016-06/15/c_135438899.htm


Beijing's health authorities confirmed [Wed 15 Jun 2016] a human case of avian influenza H7N9 in Beijing. The patient is a farmer aged 68 from Langfang City, Hebei Province. She was transferred to a Beijing hospital when her symptoms worsened, revealed the Beijing Municipal Commission of health and family planning. [The patient said she] has not had recent contact with sick poultry.

The 1st human case of the H7N9 strain of avian influenza was reported in March 2013 in China. This disease is mostly likely to occur in winter and spring. Sporadic infections have been reported, but a larger outbreak is unlikely.

Two other cases of H7N9 have been confirmed in the municipality of Tianjin. One of the patients is also a native of the city of Langfang, and the other is a resident of the Binhai New Area in Tianjin, said the Municipal Board of Health and Family Planning of Tianjin.

They were hospitalized in Tianjin after developing severe pneumonia. They both have had contact with sick poultry.

