[According to the reports above 2 cases, one hospitalized in Beijing and the other in Tianjin, have been reported as being natives of Langfang city in Hebei province. The case transferred to a Beijing hospital has no history of poultry contact. The 2 patients hospitalized in Tianjin had contact with diseased poultry.

Another 3 cases were notified by the National Health and Family Planning Commission: a case in Hebei (a male farmer from Shijiazhuang) and 2 cases in Jiangsu (a male farmer from Changzhou working in a market with poultry, and a woman from Huai'an with live poultry contact).

No additional epidemiological data are available in the reports above. - Mod.UBA

